<br>
I am going to sketch out where this is going to go from here, because I can see the process has already begun and I have experienced it myself.  A significant section of people believe that no grievance should be brought here and that those who do are &quot;just as bad&quot; as those asocial people who break the rules.  You are already being roundly condemned for posting the logs because that is beyond the pale.  These people believe that the victims of others' poor behavior are &quot;just as guilty&quot; if they vocally complain.  You were smart in that you robbed them of their usual arguments; normally, they would tear you apart for not having taken the issue to the guild's leader before bringing it here, but you did that.  But that does not matter to these people; you are still &quot;just as guilty&quot; as far as they are concerned.  There are already libelous whisperings about things you have done--things like &quot;you're no saint, I've got logs of your bad behavior but I won't post them because I'm better than you&quot;.  You will be labeled as a &quot;whiner&quot; and an &quot;asshole&quot; for having brought this issue, and later, if you have another legitimate grievance, these people will write you off completely because you are &quot;always whining&quot;, and your reputation will suffer. <p>"These discourses of heterosexuality oppress us in the sense that they prevent us from speaking unless we speak in their terms."<BR>
