<br>
Please read this and think about it so you understand where I am coming from. Those of us who are angry at Vivienne are angry because we are basing our anger on facts, not circumstantial evidence. For my part, the reason Myth's role in the training is irrelevant is because I do not know for sure whether she did or did not. THAT is why I'm not up in arms over Myth's situation, because I have not determined that she actually did or did not start the train. Thus, I can't feel passionate about her guilt or innocence. <br>
<br>
However, there are certain facts in the log, which no one has denied as being authentic. Vivienne's response to Aailin's grievance clearly shows that she knew something was going on and that she condoned whatever it was. Also, she did not deny outright that Myth did the training. Instead, she applauded such ingenuity.<br>
<br>
So, I am upset about the things I *know* to be true, not the things I don't know to be true. Does that make more sense? <br>
<br>
I don't know whether Myth trained Aailin or not. I DO know that Vivienne's response was inappropriate and inconsiderate. That's why I'm focusing on Vivienne and not on injustice done to Myth. Do you understand now?<br>
